<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-26T14:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-26T14:36:00-05:00" n="969" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d969">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13897, 13907.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-26T13:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Offices Constitutionalist Government being established in Vera Cruz.
                            General Aguilar called and congratulated me upon the orderly manner in
                            which General Funston evacuated and the clean condition in which he
                            found the city. Generals Carranza, Obregón and Alvarado announced to
                            arrive this afternoon.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>